---
const funnel = [
  { view: 'Conversation', desc: 'Mutable snapshot — one row per contact thread', color: '#0d9488' },
  { view: 'Message', desc: 'Immutable event — one row per message, forever', color: '#993C1D' },
];

const conversationInsights = [
  { title: 'Volume by channel', desc: 'How many conversations per WhatsApp, Call, Email, etc.' },
  { title: 'Growth over time', desc: 'New conversations created per day/week, via dateAdded' },
  { title: 'Current backlog', desc: 'Unread counts, open vs. assigned conversations right now' },
  { title: 'Recency', desc: 'Which threads have gone quiet, via dateUpdated / lastMessageDate' },
];

const messageInsights = [
  { title: 'Message volume', desc: 'Total messages sent/received per contact, per day, per channel' },
  { title: 'Response time', desc: 'Time between an inbound message and the outbound reply' },
  { title: 'Conversation depth', desc: 'How many messages it takes to reach a booking or a sale' },
  { title: 'Content analysis', desc: 'Keyword or sentiment trends across all message bodies over time' },
];
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>GHL Data Model — Conversations vs Messages</title>
    <style>
        :root { --accent: #0055ff; --ink: #1a1a1a; --muted: #666; --line: #e1e4e6; --teal: #0d9488; --teal-bg: #e1f5ee; --coral: #993C1D; --coral-bg: #faece7; }
        * { box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 48px 20px 64px; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.6; }
        .back-link {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 6px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: var(--accent);
            text-decoration: none;
            margin: 0 0 28px;
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: opacity 0.2s;
        }
        .back-link:hover { opacity: 0.7; }
        h1 { font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 2.6rem); margin: 16px 0 8px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
        .lede { font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.15rem); color: var(--muted); margin: 0 0 40px; max-width: 62ch; }
        .funnel-intro { font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--muted); margin: 0 0 20px; }
        .funnel { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 48px; }
        .stage { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; padding: 16px 20px; background: #fff; }
        .stage-view { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; min-width: 130px; }
        .stage-desc { color: var(--ink); font-size: 0.95rem; }
        h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin: 40px 0 6px; padding-bottom: 8px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent); }
        .section-sub { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 0 0 20px; }
        .insight-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
        .insight-card { border-radius: 10px; padding: 20px; }
        .insight-card.teal { background: var(--teal-bg); }
        .insight-card.coral { background: var(--coral-bg); }
        .insight-card h3 { margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 1rem; }
        .insight-card.teal h3 { color: var(--teal); }
        .insight-card.coral h3 { color: var(--coral); }
        .insight-card p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--ink); }
        .recap { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin: 24px 0 8px; }
        .recap-card { border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
        .recap-card h3 { margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 1.05rem; }
        .recap-card.teal h3 { color: var(--teal); }
        .recap-card.coral h3 { color: var(--coral); }
        .recap-card p { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted); }
        code { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; background: #f6f8fa; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 4px; padding: 1px 6px; font-size: 0.85em; }
        @media (max-width: 560px) {
            .stage { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 4px; }
            .stage-view { min-width: 0; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to projects</a>
    
    <h1>GHL data model: conversations vs messages</h1>
    <p class="lede">
        Working notes from analysing GoHighLevel's conversation and messaging API — the distinction between a
        mutable, current-state snapshot and an immutable, append-only historical log, and what each one is
        actually useful for.
    </p>

    <p class="funnel-intro">Two different kinds of records</p>
    <div class="funnel">
        {funnel.map((stage) => (
            <div class="stage" style={`border-left: 4px solid ${stage.color}`}>
                <span class="stage-view" style={`color: ${stage.color}`}>{stage.view}</span>
                <span class="stage-desc">{stage.desc}</span>
            </div>
        ))}
    </div>

    <h2>What happens when a message is sent</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
        Sending a WhatsApp message for the first time to a contact creates two linked objects: a new
        <code>Conversation</code> (its own <code>id</code>, <code>dateAdded</code> that never changes again,
        <code>contactId</code>) and a new <code>Message</code> (its own <code>id</code>, linked back via
        <code>conversationId</code>, carrying the body and direction). Sending a second message to the same
        contact reuses the existing conversation — only a new message row is created, and the conversation's
        summary fields (<code>lastMessageDate</code>, <code>lastMessageBody</code>) are simply overwritten.
    </p>

    <h2>What you can analyze from conversations</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Snapshot data — good for current-state and volume questions.</p>
    <div class="insight-grid">
        {conversationInsights.map((item) => (
            <div class="insight-card teal">
                <h3>{item.title}</h3>
                <p>{item.desc}</p>
            </div>
        ))}
    </div>

    <h2>What you can analyze from messages</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Historical log — good for behavior, volume-over-time, and content questions.</p>
    <div class="insight-grid">
        {messageInsights.map((item) => (
            <div class="insight-card coral">
                <h3>{item.title}</h3>
                <p>{item.desc}</p>
            </div>
        ))}
    </div>

    <h2>Recap</h2>
    <div class="recap">
        <div class="recap-card teal">
            <h3>Conversation</h3>
            <p>Current status of a thread.</p>
            <p>Overwritten with each new message.</p>
            <p>One row per contact-channel pair.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="recap-card coral">
            <h3>Message</h3>
            <p>Permanent record of one event.</p>
            <p>Never changes after creation.</p>
            <p>One row per message, forever.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Primary key & upsert logic</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
        <code>Conversation.id</code> is the primary key — one unique conversation record per contact-thread.
        When new activity happens (a new message, a tag change, anything), that same existing row is updated
        in place — overwriting <code>lastMessageDate</code>, <code>lastMessageBody</code>, <code>dateUpdated</code>,
        etc. — rather than inserting a new row. This is the upsert logic the backfill and daily sync scripts are
        built around: check if the <code>id</code> already exists, and if so, update its fields; if not, append
        it as a new row.
    </p>

</body>
</html>